Recruitment would take place during a hospital stay, with the provider intervening at the patient#$#apos;s bedside, and would make it possible to objectively assess the patient#$#apos;s profile and frailty, and to adapt treatment if necessary. The SEGAm grid could then be used [51]. It was found that frailty was associated with early readmission to hospital and the occurrence of falls [50]. Following discharge and the provision of support, continuity of the care provided during hospitalisation should be ensured, including coordination of care, communication between carers and visits to reduce early readmissions [21]. The attending physician should then be an integral part of the follow-up, with a consultation scheduled after receipt of the discharge letter within seven days, to adjust or modify treatment or care [52].Key points
